                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Consecrate yourselves therefore, and be holy, for I am the LORD your God. And you shall keep My statutes, and perform them: I am the LORD who sanctifies you.”
                                                                            <b>Leviticus 20:7-8 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“but as He who called you is holy, you also be holy in all your conduct, because it is written, “Be holy, for I am holy.”
                                                                            <b>I Peter 1:15-16 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Holiness...how do we describe holiness?  There are those who say it has the connotation of “totality.” Also it is regarded as “being morally pure”.  These are both correct, but holiness is so much more in as much as it means being separate.  God’s holiness can be described as His absolute separation from sin.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Only God is Holy and  separate from all sin. He is perfect in His nature. His character is one of flawless moral perfection.  As believers is is impossible to perceive God’s holiness because we are sinful, yet are commanded to be holy as God is holy.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">After sin...Adam and Eve could no longer live in the presence of God under the protection of Eden and were banished from the garden because they were now unholy.
                                                                            God even placing Cherubim to guard the tree of life so Adam and Eve could not live forever in a sinful state.  Another example of God’s goodness.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">God’s plan and desire to dwell with a holy people has not been thwarted.  His plan was before the foundations of the world through His Son Jesus to redeem mankind.  His desire is to have a people called by His name, to be their God and them His people and this plan will come to fruition.  He has given us the gift of Jesus, have you totally surrendered to the call to be holy in all your conduct because He is holy as stated in <b>1 Peter</b>?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Our journey through sanctification (being set apart) to growing in holiness is as the scriptures say, “we all, with unveiled face, beholding as in a mirror the glory of the Lord are being transformed into the same image from glory to glory just as by the Spirit of the Lord.  <b>2 Corinthians 3:18</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The more we grow through personal prayer, bible study, application, fellowship, servanthood, obedience we are beholding the glory of our Lord and thus we are growing from one place to higher places in Christ on the road to pure holiness.  He tells us to
                                                                            “Consecrate yourselves therefore, and be holy, for I am the LORD your God.  And you shall keep My statutes, and perform them: I am the LORD who sanctifies you.”
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">That great day will come that as Adam and Eve walked in the cool if the day with God, we shall too as stated in <b>Revelation 21:3</b>  “And I heard a loud voice saying, “Behold, the tabernacle of God is with men, and He will dwell with them, and they shall be His people.  God Himself will be with us and be our God.”  Hallelujah!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Lord God Almighty we come before You with exaltation in our hearts as we praise and honor You.  Holy, holy, holy are You Lord God Almighty.  Teach us Lord to understand what it means to be set apart for Your purposes.  Search us O God and know our hearts; try us and know our  anxieties; and see if there is any wickedness in us, and lead us in the way everlasting.  Lead us to a walk of holiness for Your honor, we pray Father we are willing.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">In Jesus name...Amen.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>





